Summary: Caught in a picture of the planets, kind of honey come shape.
divs: Sighting DetailsI like to capture the stars, or planets and observe them on my computer by enlarging them. That is when I began observing these honey come shaped little white spots. I thought they were bugs at first, but they were as far out as the planets. I capture one almost every time I take a picture at night. I would like for you to investigate this and tell us what we are capturing on camera. This is very strange, also I have pictures of somethings like worm holes with circles of light pulsating another light into it.
